# @COMMENT: There are several scribal errors on the *isnād* for this fragment. The name Yazīd b. Hārūn is rendered "يزيد بن هرون" and Muḥammad b. Isḥāq is rendered as "محمد بن اسحق." Giving Ibn Isḥāq's name without the *alif* is not uncommon. Also, Ismāʿīl b. ʿUlayah is given as "إسماعيل بن إبراهيم."

